# Meet your micro:bit - Lesson Overview

<p style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold;"> Carefully read over the entire <a href="https://code.org/maker/assets/CSF-Booklet-Course-C-Nov2023.pdf" target="_blank" style="color: #8C52BA;">lesson plan</a> before you begin teaching.</p>


## What your students will learn

<img src="https://images.code.org/44bf037c42889ba3ff0038810da2a3a8-image-1707234436320.png" alt="cartoon style drawing of a student holding a micro:bit" width="300px" style="border-radius:10px; float:right; margin: 0 0 40px 40px;">

#### This lesson is a prerequisite for teaching the coding lessons. 

#### It helps reinforce what your students already know about code and computing concepts by transferring them to the physical world through exploring preprogrammed micro:bits.


## Lesson preparation 
#### The lesson requires some short preparation to transfer the exploratory project onto micro:bits:

 - #### <p style="font-size: 13pt;">Rewatch the download instructions in the <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=X3zxNSIFsdQ?start=60" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: 8C52BA;">video</a> starting at 1 minute.</p> 
 - #### Download the Meet your micro:bit <a href = "https://mbit.io/csf-1-project" target = "blank"  rel="noopener noreferrer">program</a> onto micro:bits 
 
